org.integratedmodelling.thinklab.api.knowledge
Interface IKnowledgeSubject

All Superinterfaces:
IKnowledge, IResource
All Known Subinterfaces:
IConcept, IInstance
public interface IKnowledgeSubject
extends IKnowledge

Extends IKnowledge to define "subjects", meaning first-class objects that have a right to exist independently in a knowledge space. This includes IConcept and IInstance but not IProperty, as we see properties as connectors for KnowledgeSubject that should not exist alone. KnowledgeSubject has semantic types, annotations, and relationship access methods. FIXME this interface is in dire need of a better name.

Author:
Ferdinando Villa

get

IValue get(java.lang.String property)
           throws ThinklabException
The basic function to extract the value of a property. Could have a better name but it's so basic that I like a basic name. The IValue returned will be of the proper type; if the property has more than one value on this object, the IValue will be a ListValue.
